cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the structure of file sharing communities and their access patterns, which falls under the scope of social networks and data mining. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also analyzes the graphs of these communities, which involves concepts from graph theory and algorithms, making cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of web caches and content distribution networks, which falls under the scope of computer networks, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) a possible category. Finally, the paper proposes ways to design mechanisms that exploit the naturally emerging patterns, which involves concepts from artificial intelligence and machine learning, making cs.CY (Computational Complexity) a possible category as well.
